 {
 "String": "Four known or suspected metabolites of cyclohexane (cyclohexanol, cyclohexanone, 1,4-cyclohexanediol and 1,4-cyclohexanedione) were also studied for kidney effects. These compounds were administered at a daily dose of 0.5 g/kg (5 I.P. injections per week for two weeks). Only cyclohexanol increased beta-2-microglobulin which suggests that this metabolite is responsible for the kidney effects of cyclohexane.",
