 {
 "String": "URBAN/SUBURBAN: Cyclohexane was detected in 37.5% of the samples collected in Washington, DC, March 1991, at a mean and maximum concentrations of 0.42 and 10.8 ppbV, respectively(1). It was detected in 9 or 12 rural air samples in LA, 1990, at concentrations ranging from 0.3 to 1.5 ppbV(2). Cyclohexane was detected at an average concentration of approximately 2 ppbC in Atlanta air samples, Aug-Sep, 1992(3). Based on measurements from 39 US cities, 1984-85, the atmospheric concentration of cyclohexane ranged from 0.2 to 409 ppbC with a median concentration of 2.2 ppbC(4). The average concentration of cyclohexane in roadway samples near Raleigh, NC, 1983, was 0.39% of the total non-methane hydrocarbon concentration(5). Cyclohexane was detected in 120 of 129 samples collected across Canada, Nov 90 to Dec 91, at concentrations ranging from 0.01 to 0.12 ppbV(6). The average concentration of cyclohexane at street level in London, 1988, was 2.3 ppb(7). Cyclohexane was qualitatively found in 4 of 8 personal air samples of subjects monitored in Bayonne and Elizabeth, NJ, and Research Triangle Park, NC, 1980(8).",
