 {
 "String": "In 2010, 137 workers at the Suzhou facility of Wintek in China, one of Apple's iPhone suppliers, suffered adverse health effects following exposure to n-hexane, a chemical used in cleaning in some manufacturing processes. The factory had reconfigured operations without also changing their ventilation system. Apple required Wintek to stop using n-hexane and to provide evidence that they had removed the chemical from their production lines. In addition, Apple required them to fix their ventilation system.",
