 "String": "RURAL/REMOTE: The respective median, minimum and maximum atmospheric concentrations of n-hexane for 5 rural locations in NC ranged from 0.2 to 7.5, 0.1 to 5.8, and 0.7 to 10.6 ppb, respectively(1). n-Hexane was identified, not quantified, in the atmospheres of downtown Tuscaloosa, AL and a rural site 35 miles away, the Talladega National Forest from December 1976 through 1977(2). The atmospheric concentration of n-hexane at the Jones State Forest in rural TX was 4.1 ppb in 1978(3). The average concentration of n-hexane at a rural site in Northern Berlin, Germany was 0.33 ug/cu m(4). The average n-hexane concentration for samples taken at altitudes of 300 to 2,500 ft over Lake Michigan on Aug 27, 1976 was 0.5 ppb(1). The average n-hexane concentration for samples taken at altitudes of 1,000 and 1,500 ft over Lake Michigan on Aug 28, 1976 was 0.4 ppb(5). The air over the Norwegian Arctic had an average n-hexane concentration of 172 parts per trillion in the spring of 1983(6).",
