 "Value": {
 "StringWithMarkup": [
 {
 "String": "The average emission of cyclohexane from gasoline in S. California, 1987, was 0.37% of the total non-methane hydrocarbon concentration(1); in Chicago, 1990, it was 0.7%(2). Cyclohexane emissions were found to be 0.4% and 0% of total organic emission for catalyst and non-catalyst auto engines, respectively(3). It was detected in exhaust of 1975-1982 model passenger vehicles(4). Cyclohexane was detected as an emission from Oklahoma oil fields, 1988, at an average concentration of 2.1 ppbC(5). The emissions of wastewater sludge composting facility contained cyclohexane at a concentration of 327 ug/cu m(6). The average concentration of cyclohexane in the exhaust of 6 cars in the UK, 1988, was 82 ppb(7). Cyclohexane was qualitatively detected as an emission from 5 hazardous waste sites and a landfill in NJ, date not provided(8). Cyclohexane was qualitatively detected in 39/81 categories of common household products(9,10). Cyclohexane emissions have been associated with architectural and industrial coatings(1) and gasoline refineries(2). Cyclohexane was detected at concentrations of 4-31 mg/cu m in landfill gas emissions at 7 sites in the United Kingdom(11). Monitoring of vehicle emissions in road tunnels of Sao Paulo, Brazil in 2004 detected a mean cyclohexane emission factor of 81.3 mg/km(12).",
