 {
 "String": "INDOOR: According to the VOC national ambient database, updated in 1986, cyclohexane was detected in 4 indoor air samples ranging from 0.4 to 2.3 ppbv with an average concentration of 1.38 ppbV(1). Cyclohexane was detected in new or recently renovated buildings in Switzerland, at a maximum concentration of 7162 ug/cu m(2). Cyclohexane was qualitatively detected in houses that had recently used an oil-based floor finish(3). The mean concentration of cyclohexane in indoor air of 3 Italian cities, March, 1995, was 4.5, 5.7, and 5.6 ug/cu m(4). Cyclohexane concentrations of 340-380 ug/cu m were detected in living room and bedroom air of homes in Melbourne, Australia 2 days after construction(5); concentrations fell to <1 ug/cu 17 days later(5). A mean cyclohexane concentration of 2.90 ug/cu (maximum concentration 52 ug/cu m) was detected in indoor air of homes in suburban and rural New Jersey(6). Cyclohexane was detected (detection limit of 0.015 ug/cu m) in indoor air samples at 70 of 75 homes in Ottawa, Canada during winter 2002-2003 monitoring at a concentration range of 0.015-54.12 ug/cu m (mean concentration of 6.58 ug/cu m)(7).",
